The flight is a likely indication that delivery for the Moroccan flag-carrier is in sight after years of waiting. The airline was originally scheduled to be one of the earliest customers of the Dreamliner, ordering four airplanes in 2005. The first aircraft appeared painted and ready to fly in the spring of 2010, where it has remained since.RAM elected to defer the jets in September of 2012 as the airline faced extensive financial pressure. It currently has four 787-8s on order.